=== Nutrition ===

A {{convert|100|g|oz|abbr=off|adj=on|frac=2}} reference serving of rye provides {{convert|338|kcal|kJ|order=flip|abbr=off}} of [[food energy]] and is a rich source (20% or more of the [[Daily Value]], DV) of [[essential nutrients]], including [[protein]], [[dietary fiber]], the [[B vitamins]], [[niacin]] (27% DV) and [[vitamin B6|vitamin B&lt;sub&gt;6&lt;/sub&gt;]] (23% DV), and several [[dietary minerals]] (table). Highest nutrient contents are for [[manganese]] (143% DV) and [[phosphorus]] (47% DV) (table).

